    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-06-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-06-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="953"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d953">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.00/1616.</note>
                <head>[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-06-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 9, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I earnestly request <hi rend="italic">Yorktown</hi> remain at Corinto two weeks
                    at least, on account of activities of Zelayistas in Costa Rica reported to this
                    Government. Castro Quesada, Costa Rican minister foreign affairs, is said to be
                    aiding them.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Northcott.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
